com.github.sviperll.adt4j

Annotation Type GenerateValueClassForVisitor


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Documented
public @interface GenerateValueClassForVisitor
    Generates value class for annotated visitor-interface.
    Author:
    Victor Nazarov <asviraspossible@gmail.com>
    See Also:
    ADT4J project page

    • Element Detail

      • acceptMethodName

        public abstract String acceptMethodName
        Name of generated accept-method.

        Accept method perform actual "visit".

        Returns:
        Name of generated accept-method
        Default:
        "accept"

      • acceptMethodAccess

        public abstract MemberAccess acceptMethodAccess
        Java's access modifier for generated accept-method.

        Accept method perform actual "visit".

        Default is public.

        Returns:
        Java's access modifier for generated accept-method.
        Default:
        com.github.sviperll.adt4j.MemberAccess.PUBLIC

      • className

        public abstract String className
        Name of generated class (algebraic data type).

        You can leave className parameter out. Generated class name is chosen by removing "Visitor"-suffix from visitor-interface name. If visitor-interface name doesn't end with "Visitor", "Value"-suffix is appended to visitor-interface name to form generated class name.

        Returns:
        Name of generated class (algebraic data type).
        Default:
        ":auto"

      • implementsInterfaces

        public abstract Class<?>[] implementsInterfaces
        Interfaces for value classes to implement.

        You can leave the implementsInterfaces parameter out. Generated classes will implement these interfaces, allowing the developer to work with abstractions, and make use of Java 8 default methods.

        Returns:
        Class name of marker interface.
        Default:
        {}

      • extendsClass

        public abstract Class<?> extendsClass
        Class for value classes to extend.

        You can leave the extendsClass parameter out. Generated classes will extends this class, allowing the developer to work with abstractions, and make use of Java 8 default methods.

        Returns:
        Class name of marker interface.
        Default:
        java.lang.Object.class

      • isPublic

        public abstract boolean isPublic
        Java's access for generated class.

        Public or package-private.

        Default name is package-private

        Returns:
        Java's access for generated class.
        Default:
        false

      • hashCodeBase

        public abstract int hashCodeBase
        Base integer to perform hash code evaluation in generated class.

        Should be prime for better results.

        Returns:
        Base integer to perform hash code evaluation in generated class.
        Default:
        37

      • hashCodeCaching

        public abstract Caching hashCodeCaching
        hashCode method caching strategy.

        You should probably always use NONE caching, until you actually need some hashCode speedup.

        The only case when strategy can be anything but NONE is when all fields are actually immutable.

        PRECOMPUTE strategy can potentially speed up equals method

        See Also:
        Caching
        Default:
        com.github.sviperll.adt4j.Caching.NONE

      • isSerializable

        public abstract boolean isSerializable
        Specifies weather generated class should be serializable.
        Returns:
        weather generated class should be serializable.
        Default:
        false

      • isComparable

        public abstract boolean isComparable

      • serialVersionUID

        public abstract long serialVersionUID
